cli/output/user_settings.go exports UserSettings{Theme string}, LoadUserSettings(sess *fileio.Session) (UserSettings, error), and SaveUserSettings(sess *fileio.Session, settings UserSettings) error. Reads/writes .drift/user-settings.xml via the Session in the format &lt;settings&gt;&lt;theme&gt;NAME&lt;/theme&gt;&lt;/settings&gt;. Returns (UserSettings{}, nil) if the file does not exist — this is the normal case for fresh projects. The file is NOT committed to git (listed in .drift/.gitignore, created by drift init). Created by `drift config theme NAME`. Consumed by resolveTheme during SelectPresenter (see <ref spec="output.custom_theme">theme resolution</ref> and <ref spec="fileio.session">fileio.Session</ref>).